# 📤 Outputs

## 📂 Contents of the `out/` folder

| File                                | What it is                                               | Why it matters                   |
| ----------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `agent1_cohort_findings.md`         | Markdown table of high-risk visits identified by Agent 1 | Shows exact cohort selection     |
| `agent1_tool_trace.json`            | Tool call trace (function + arguments + output)          | Verifies tool usage occurred     |
| `retrieval_payload.json`            | Structured RAG data passed to the LLM                    | Shows exactly what the model saw |
| `retrieval_verification.json`       | Machine-readable validation of retrieval vs SQL          | Ensures correctness              |
| `retrieval_verification.md`         | Human-readable validation summary                        | Easy inspection of results       |
| `homework2_comprehensive_report.md` | Final clinical report generated by Agent 2               | Main system output               |

---

## 🧠 Understanding the pipeline via outputs

You can trace the entire workflow:

1. Cohort selection → `agent1_cohort_findings.md`
2. Tool verification → `agent1_tool_trace.json`
3. Retrieval data → `retrieval_payload.json`
4. Validation → `retrieval_verification.*`
5. Final report → `homework2_comprehensive_report.md`

